ChIP-seq data analysis

load the required library to carry out the analysis.

library(ChIPseeker)
library(rtracklayer)
library(TxDb.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg38.knownGene)
library(clusterProfiler)
txdb <- TxDb.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg38.knownGene

load the files and name them accordingly.

## $ENCFF418TUX
## [1] "ENCFF418TUX.bed.gz"
## 
## $ENCFF791SNR
## [1] "ENCFF791SNR.bed.gz"

Lets annotate the peak to find the genomic features.

peakAnnoList <- lapply(files, annotatePeak, TxDb=txdb,
                       tssRegion=c(-3000, 3000), verbose=FALSE)

plotAnnoBar(peakAnnoList)

A venn diagram to compare the overlapping binding sites in the two datatset.

genes= lapply(peakAnnoList, function(i) as.data.frame(i)$geneId)
vennplot(genes)

Compare the TSS region the dataset.

promoter <- getPromoters(TxDb=txdb, upstream=3000, downstream=3000)

tagMatrixList <- lapply(files, getTagMatrix, windows=promoter)

plotAvgProf(tagMatrixList, xlim=c(-3000, 3000))

lets view the TSS region separately in each dataset

plotAvgProf(tagMatrixList, xlim = c(-3000, 3000), conf = 0.95, resample = 500, facet = "row")
>> Running bootstrapping for tag matrix...       2021-01-29 1:05:01 PM 
>> Running bootstrapping for tag matrix...       2021-01-29 1:06:19 PM

lets do the pathway enrichment analysis.

genes = lapply(peakAnnoList, function(i) as.data.frame(i)$geneId)
names(genes) = sub("_", "\n", names(genes))
compKEGG <- compareCluster(geneCluster = genes, fun = "enrichKEGG", pvalueCutoff = 0.05, 
    pAdjustMethod = "BH")
dotplot(compKEGG, showCategory = 15, title = "KEGG Pathway Enrichment Analysis")

8 pathways which are exhibited by the sample ENCFF791SNR is not expressed in the other sample ENCFF418TUX and 12 pathways which were expressed in sample ENCFF418TUX is not expressed in ENCFF791SNR. Both the samples seems to behave differently.Sample ENCFF418TUX exhibit the Rap1 signaling pathway which is involved in tumor cell invasion and metastasis.ENCFF791SNR exhibit the expression of Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis which is a type of motor neuron disease.
